metadata.name: Veni
metadata.description:
The first piece is "Veni," which means "come. The first action of man before his next steps. We come at the very beginning. And our first step is to come. These works were written under the impression of Julius Caesar's quick victory. And carry with them a kind of subtext of our essence. The plays are divided into three stages
1. Veni - come.
2. Vidi - see.
3. Vici - won

2.183 x 3.006 px
